    <section id="introduction">
        <h2>Introduction:</h2>
        <p>I'm a big fan of Taipei’s riverside parks, and one of the best places to witness a stunning sunset is Sunset Spot Title. Situated at the crossroads of Zhongshan, Neihu, and Songshan, Sunset Spot Title is a vast park that offers ample space for various activities.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="activities">
        <h2>Activities at Sunset Spot Title:</h2>
        <p>At Sunset Spot Title, you'll find people engaging in sports, picnicking, running, walking their dogs, and biking. The park provides a panoramic view of Taipei's urban landscape, including planes landing at Songshan Airport, traffic jams on the highway, Taipei 101 towering over the city, blooming flowers, boats floating on the river, and the majestic Grand Hotel Taipei behind the beautiful Dazhi Bridge.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="photography">
        <h2>Sunset Photography:</h2>
        <p>Sunset Spot Title offers diverse options for capturing sunset pictures. You can walk along the river and capture the bridge and Grand Hotel in the background, use the park’s trees as foreground reference points, or even take creative shots from behind the basketball court to capture some action during the sunset.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="accessibility">
        <h2>Accessibility:</h2>
        <p>If you don’t live near Neihu, Sunset Spot Title is accessible by public transit. Take the MRT to Jiannan Road Station and walk about 15 minutes to the park. You can also use YouBikes available at the MRT station for quick access within the park. Alternatively, buses from MRT Jiannan Road Station can take you directly to the park.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="transportation">
        <h2>Transportation Details:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Nearest Station: Dazhi Meiti Garden 3 | Last bus R3: 23:00</li>
            <li>Dazhi Meiti Garden 2 | Last bus 42: 19:00 weekdays, 18:30 weekends</li>
            <li>MRT Jiannan Road Station | Last Brown Line train: 00:20 towards Taipei Zoo; 00:49 towards Nangang Exhibition Center</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="parking">
        <h2>Parking Information:</h2>
        <p>There is parking available inside the park.</p>
    </section>

